add("This warrant matters because OULAD, like most learning-analytics data, records behaviour exhaustively yet contains no direct psychometric measure of motivation, self-efficacy, or task value. Bridging the gap requires theory-grounded proxies—indicators linked to motivational constructs by prior evidence rather than assumed post hoc. Reviews of technology-mediated engagement support this strategy, showing that log-derived behavioural indicators are valid, if partial, operationalisations of the processes that underpin learning (Henrie et al., 2015). The MPI is therefore a deliberately theory-driven composite rather than a data-mined aggregate, each dimension justified independently against the SDT–EVT–SRL framework.",
"Because OULAD records behaviour exhaustively yet measures no motivation, self-efficacy, or task value directly, bridging the gap requires theory-grounded proxies—indicators linked to motivational constructs by prior evidence, not assumed post hoc. Reviews of technology-mediated engagement support this: log-derived indicators are valid, if partial, operationalisations of the processes underpinning learning (Henrie et al., 2015). The MPI is therefore a theory-driven composite, not a data-mined aggregate, each dimension justified independently against the SDT–EVT–SRL framework.")

